> Paul,
> We can defiantly tell the 1700lb clutch over stock, and another vw
> friend has stopped using the 1700 lb because he was braking a clutch
> every year or less.
> Stock clutch is like butter and 1700lb you know you are pushing.
> Hope this helps
> P & C

One problem with the stiff clutches is that the added pedal effort
increases stress on the entire system.

Unless you have a really powerful engine, it is unlikely that you will
slip a stock clutch, so stock is usually better.

George
